"a": "HLA-G is expressed almost exclusively by extravillous trophoblast (and as early as the 2-cell stage). It inhibits NK-cell-mediated and cytotoxic T-cell killing of trophoblast, promotes immunoregulatory cytokines and angiogenesis, and is key to implantation. Its deficiency/absence is associated with recurrent implantation failure and recurrent miscarriage.",
