"a": "It quantifies fetomaternal haemorrhage by detecting fetal red cells in maternal blood. On acid elution, fetal haemoglobin resists the acid and fetal cells retain their stain (pink), whereas adult maternal cells lose colour (ghost cells), allowing the volume of fetal cells to be quantified (to guide anti-D dosing).",
